    <p>When you have a com­pact home, it’s es­sen­tial to have a setup that can be ti­died and re­ar­ranged in a snap when guests are com­ing over. Wheels can come in handy on ta­bles, the kitchen is­land and stor­age boxes when they need to be moved around or put away.</p>
    <p>A lack of square footage doesn’t mean you have to go for tiny fur­ni­ture. Con­versely, a hodge­podge of small items can cre­ate vis­ual clut­ter. While you should still get fur­ni­ture that’s pro­por­tion­ate to the space, stick to a few promi­nent pieces for a well-cu­rated and un­clut­tered look.</p>

